  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    DataTypeException
    Subtype of SyntaxException for syntax errors having to do with misuse of data type (for example, assigning a String value to an int variable or casting to void type).
    InternalCompilerException  
    InternalParserException
    An exception representing an error within the parser (or AST generation) code itself.
    ParseException
    A SyntaxException for the case when the input cannot be parsed, i.e.
    ScanException
    A SyntaxException for the case when the input cannot be scanned (lexed/tokenized), for exmaple if an invalid character is present in the input file.
    SyntaxException
    Superclass of exceptions representing syntax errors in the input file.
